The paper discusses attacks on the security of computer systems, specifically related to speculative execution. This makes it likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the violation of security assumptions in software security mechanisms, which could also place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for updates to instruction set architectures, which could place it in the cs.AR (Architecture) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for fixes to processor designs, which could place it in the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of these attacks on actual systems, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
